cff-version: 1.2.0
message: >-
  This repository is a fork of SharpAI/SwiftLM extended with TurboQuant
  weight + KV cache compression and Bonjour-based distributed cluster
  support. Citations should distinguish the base server (cite the
  upstream SharpAI/SwiftLM project) from the fork's additions (this
  CITATION.cff). GitHub renders a "Cite this repository" button that
  reads this file and produces BibTeX / APA exports.
title: "SwiftLM (TurboQuant + Distributed Fork)"
abstract: >-
  Fork of SwiftLM — a native Swift, OpenAI-compatible inference server
  for Apple MLX models — with TurboQuant weight and KV cache
  compression integrated and a Bonjour-based multi-Mac distributed
  inference runtime added. Research-relevant additions include the
  origin-keyed codebook validation scheme, the two-stage Argon2id +
  HKDF cluster authentication design, the cluster UUID as shared
  Argon2 salt, and the file-first cluster key storage with Bonjour
  propagation as the primary key-distribution path.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Kovshilovsky
    given-names: Eugene
    description: "Fork maintainer; TurboQuant and distributed additions"
version: "0.1.0"
date-released: "2026-04-17"
license: MIT
keywords:
  - swift
  - mlx
  - openai-api
  - apple-silicon
  - inference
  - distributed-inference
  - quantization
  - turboquant
  - bonjour
  - cluster-authentication
repository-code: "https://github.com/SharpAI/SwiftLM"
